# Code owners — the approval gate for the canonical runtime registry.
#
# In this repo, a runtime is *accepted* when its manifest is merged under
# `registry/runtimes/`. Requiring code-owner review on that path (with branch
# protection's "Require review from Code Owners" enabled) is what makes a merge
# equivalent to approval. See GOVERNANCE.md.
#
# Owners: @BunsDev and @romgenie (repo maintainers, both with write access).
# Two owners means either can review the other's PRs, so protected-path changes
# stay mergeable under enforce_admins. To govern via the org's
# @OpenCoven/maintainers team instead, grant that team write access to this repo
# and swap the handles below (granting team access needs the `admin:org` scope).

# The accepted-runtime source manifests: acceptance decisions live here.
/registry/                              @BunsDev @romgenie

# The compiled index is generated — guard it so it can only change via a rebuild
# reviewed alongside its source manifest.
/crates/coven-runtime-registry/canonical/  @BunsDev @romgenie

# The SDK crates and shared spec/schema.
/crates/                                @BunsDev @romgenie
/schema/                                @BunsDev @romgenie

# Governance, acceptance criteria, and the release/publish pipeline.
/GOVERNANCE.md                          @BunsDev @romgenie
/.github/                               @BunsDev @romgenie
